.TH CWE-306 7 "2025-12-11" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-306 \- Missing Authentication for Critical Function
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#21\fR (2024 rank: 25).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Authentication.
.SH DESCRIPTION
A critical function is reachable without authentication: admin panels, debug interfaces, firmware\-update or internal APIs are exposed so any actor who can reach the network path can invoke them.
.SH MITIGATION
Require authentication for every sensitive function and verify it server\-side; do not rely on an endpoint being hidden. Combine with authorization and an extra factor for the most dangerous operations.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
CISA KEV catalog (as of 2026-06-15): \fB35\fR exploited CVEs mapped to this weakness.
.PP
CVE\-2019\-5591, CVE\-2019\-9082, CVE\-2020\-3952, CVE\-2020\-6207, CVE\-2020\-6287, CVE\-2020\-13927, CVE\-2020\-24363, CVE\-2021\-20021, CVE\-2021\-37415, CVE\-2021\-44077, CVE\-2022\-1388, CVE\-2022\-21587, CVE\-2022\-23227, CVE\-2022\-24990, CVE\-2022\-26143, CVE\-2022\-26501, CVE\-2022\-26925, CVE\-2023\-27532, CVE\-2023\-28461, CVE\-2023\-36846, CVE\-2023\-36847, CVE\-2023\-36851, CVE\-2024\-0012, CVE\-2024\-5910, CVE\-2024\-47575, CVE\-2025\-0108, CVE\-2025\-3248, CVE\-2025\-4008, CVE\-2025\-32433, CVE\-2025\-61757, CVE\-2026\-24423, CVE\-2026\-33017, CVE\-2026\-35273, CVE\-2026\-39987, CVE\-2026\-41940.
.SH EXAMPLES
One vulnerable\->fixed pair per ecosystem (Node.js, Python, Java, Go, PHP).
.SS Node.js
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
app.post('/admin/shutdown', (req, res) => {   // no auth
  systemShutdown();
  res.send('bye');
});
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
app.post('/admin/shutdown', requireAuth, requireRole('admin'), (req, res) => {
  systemShutdown();
  res.send('bye');
});
.EE
.RE
.SS Python
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
@app.post('/admin/shutdown')   # no auth
def shutdown():
    system_shutdown()
    return 'bye'
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
@app.post('/admin/shutdown')
@login_required
@require_role('admin')
def shutdown():
    system_shutdown()
    return 'bye'
.EE
.RE
.SS Java
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
// Spring Security
http.authorizeHttpRequests(a -> a.requestMatchers("/admin/**").permitAll());
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
http.authorizeHttpRequests(a -> a
    .requestMatchers("/admin/**").hasRole("ADMIN")   // authenticated + authorized
    .anyRequest().authenticated());
.EE
.RE
.SS Go
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
http.HandleFunc("/admin/shutdown", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    systemShutdown()   // no auth
})
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
http.Handle("/admin/shutdown", requireRole("admin",
  http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
      systemShutdown()
  })))
.EE
.RE
.SS PHP
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
// admin_shutdown.php - no auth
system_shutdown();
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
if (empty($_SESSION['user']) || ($_SESSION['role'] ?? '') !== 'admin') {
    http_response_code(401); exit;
}
system_shutdown();
.EE
.RE
